==English==
===Noun Phrase===
'''present participle'''

#(''Grammar'') A verb form ending with the suffix ''[[-ing]]'' that indicates an ongoing action or state in the present.  A present participle functions as an adjective, and can be preceded by a form of the verb ''to [[be]]'' to make the [[progressive tense]]s of a verb.

